# What Vercel SHOULD upload
#
# Runtime + build code: app/, components/, server/, shared/, styles/,
# prisma/, eslint-rules/, plus root configs (next.config.mjs,
# package.json, pnpm-lock.yaml, tsconfig.json, postcss.config.mjs,
# globals.d.ts, prisma.config.ts, vercel.json).
#
# Everything below is bloat. Each entry trims the upload size, which
# matters because Vercel's free-tier `api-upload-free` quota counts
# files (not megabytes). A typical pre-trim deploy uploaded 5,000+
# files; with these rules the count drops well below the daily cap.
#
# `.gitignore` is honoured automatically — no need to repeat
# node_modules/, .next/, coverage/, .env*, etc here.

# ── Documentation (~5 MB, never read at runtime) ────────────────────────
docs/
*.md
!README.md

# ── Tests (~1 MB, only used by Vitest in dev / CI) ──────────────────────
tests/
**/*.test.ts
**/*.test.tsx
**/*.spec.ts
**/*.spec.tsx
vitest.config.ts
vitest.config.mts

# ── Custom scripts (run manually against the DB, not at boot) ───────────
# Note: scripts/ is NOT imported by app/ or server/ — verified via grep.
# `pnpm db:seed` is run manually from a developer machine with
# DIRECT_URL set, never in Vercel's build / runtime path.
#
# Exception: `vercel-ignore-build.sh` IS read by Vercel's "Ignored
# Build Step" before the build starts. Without the negation below,
# Vercel strips the script via .vercelignore and then errors with
# "No such file or directory" when it tries to execute it.
scripts/
!scripts/vercel-ignore-build.sh

# ── Dev tooling (not used at build or runtime) ──────────────────────────
.claude/
.husky/
.github/
.editorconfig
.gitleaks.toml
.prettierrc
.prettierignore
.lintstagedrc.json
codecov.yml
commitlint.config.js
import-docs.sh
.env.example

# ── IDE / OS noise ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
*.swp
*.swo
.vscode/
.idea/
